node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Emilie Ristevski on September 08, 2021 tagging @helloemilie, and @willandbear. May be an image of standing and nature.

node.text:
The raw beauty of this otherworldly volcanic landscape… ✨🤍☁️ EXCITING ANNOUNCEMENT — My friends at @willandbear have just launched an incredible content creator contest with over $10k worth of prizes to win! 

Photographers, storytellers, filmmakers, and creatives of every description, in any place @willandbear invite you to share your moments captured! The winner will receive 5k cash + a @sonyalpha.anz Alpha 7C + 29-60mm kit lens + Master Class with @stefan_haworth

Link in bio + stories to enter! #willandbear #momentscaptured #sonyalphaANZ #photochallenge 
(Entries open worldwide! Closes at midnight on 21st Sept AEST. Full T&C's on the entry page).

node.text:
Let me transport you to our Natural World. Locations below:

1. Vestrahorn, Iceland
2. Dolomites, Italy
3. Tasmania, Australia
4. Skógafoss, Iceland
5. My backyard (Australia)
6. Italian Alps
7. Byron Bay Hinterland, New South Whales 
8. Tasmanian Highlands
9. Scenic Rim, Queensland 
10. Mount Hood, Pacific North West

.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#reels #reelsinstagram #traveldeeper #wanderlusters #momentsinthewild #travel #wanderlust #searchwandercollect #exploremore #lovetheworld #nature #icelandnature #travelinspo

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Emilie Ristevski on September 05, 2021 tagging @helloemilie. May be an image of body of water.

node.text:
Desert textures from above… ✨🧡🌈
These type of landscapes always leave me full of curiosity. Deep burnt oranges entwine with golden honey & yellows – Mother Nature is always the best artist.

node.text: The changing of seasons…✨☁️🌈🌙 wrapped in @wanderingfolk — the most stunning picnic rugs & throws. Awaking before dawn, as a layer of mist surrounds the mountain valleys. The warmth of the rising sun transforms the sky and land — I’m forever grateful for Mother Nature and the ever-changing wonders hidden all around us.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Emilie Ristevski on August 31, 2021. May be a closeup of nature and sky.

node.text: Moon-shine & mountain dusk… ✨🌈🌸🌙 Each time I glance up at the moon, it reminds me of how tiny we are and how we all exist together in this universe. There is an unspoken sense of interconnection we all hold under the same sky.

node.text:
The burnt orange tones of Namibia… ✨🧡 

I’ve loved seeing the entries for the #MyNuiiAdventure photography contest! Final reminder it will be ending on September 6th & offers an amazing chance to experience a trip to Namibia!

This is a special opportunity to join the conservation adventure and a desert elephant expedition to learn first hand about the critically-endangered desert elephant population. Each year @Nuii_Icecream_Global is committed to supporting biodiversity projects in wild places where they can make a real difference to the lives of people & animals as well as their environment. Wild places are a huge source of inspiration for us and it’s important we give back in some way. 

I can’t wait to help to choose the winner – Head to the @Nuii_Icecream_Global to read the full terms and conditions and find out more! #MyNuiiAdventure

node.text:
A tribute, apology, and thank you to our Planet Earth ✨🌿🌎 Nature gives us so much, despite how much we take. We have much to learn & nature can teach us, if we choose to listen... Filled with wonder I looked out towards the coastline, a place which feels like the edge of the world. Surrounded by wild rivers, jagged mountain ranges, button grass plains and ancient rainforest. These landscapes in Tasmania are some of the most wild, isolated and remote in all of Australia.

In partnership with @volvocars for #ForEveryonesSafety, a global initiative helping to talk about how we are all a part of the problem, but how we can equally be part of the solution. #VolvoCars have committed to the highest standard of sustainability and by pursuing a science-based carbon reduction plan they aim to become climate neutral by 2040. 

For each and every little thing we all do to tread lightly on this place we call home —The smallest actions create ripple effects and together we all have the ability to create real impact to help protect these special places. Learn more by visiting the link in @volvocars page.

.
.
.
.
.
#reels #reelsinstagram #stayandwander #traveldeeper #wanderlove  #momentsinthewild #traveldeeper #travel #wanderlust #searchwandercollect #exploremore #lovetheworld #nature #visualsofearth #planetearth #protectorsofourplanet

node.text:
A love letter to one of my favourite places on our planet…Tasmania, Australia. ✨🌾🌈💛 This past year of slowing down has meant a whole new level of self reflection but also of appreciation – more appreciation than ever before for our planet and the special places on earth we must cherish and protect.

I’ve teamed up with @volvocars for their new initiative #ForEveryonesSafety. A global initiative helping to talk about how we are all a part of the problem, but how we can equally be part of the solution. #VolvoCars are ready to move forward with a new sense of accountability and lead the industry’s transition to zero emission mobility, which is key to reaching global net zero emissions by 2050. 

By continuing to connect with our natural world I hope more of us can understand why we need to protect these special places and rethink the ways we can all help to be a part of the solutions. To learn more about what we can all do to make the world a safer place visit the link in @volvocars.

Wanderings in the golden desert…✨🌞💛🧡 I love the creative energy that forms when deeply connecting and exploring with like minded people. 

I’m judging a new PHOTOGRAPHY COMPETITION with @nuii_icecream_global ending on September 6th! We are seeking out your most inspiring travel photos, whether that be far or close to home. We are seeking out your most inspiring travel photos, whether that be far or close to home. It could be your favourite travel memory from a trip that changed your life, or something completely new you discovered only a couple minutes from your door. 

Best of all this project offers the winner a once in a lifetime trip to Namibia with @wild.ark and @ehranamibia! Entering is as easy as sharing your photo with #MyNuiiAdventure & @nuii_icecream_global. We are looking for the images taken off the beaten path, wilder than the everyday and hopefully unique and unexpected – Can’t wait to see your photos!
